               <note type="description">According to Michel Chodkiewicz, this is an esoteric commentary upon the Fātiḥa which completes Chapter 383 of FM which, in the series of ‘waystations’ (manāzil), corresponds to the waystation of the Fātiha.</note>
               <note type="biblioComments">A much copied work, verified by at least five historic mss. The best is Veliyuddin 1759, which is a holograph with two samāʿs in the presence of IA, one dated 617H in Aleppo, the other dated 627H (Damascus). The title on Beyazit 3750 (253b) says that the work is one of the manāzil in FM; we have checked against the holograph and it is identical. Perhaps needs some further checking (see OY’s comment on p.179).</note>
